                <p>The cumin and coriander seeds are generally used roasted The various materials
                    are cleaned, dried, ground, sifted, thoroughly mixed, and bottled. Upwards of
                    forty different methods of preparing curry are given in the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Indian Domestic Economy and Receipt Book,</hi> 2d ed. Madras, 1850.</p>
